Paper: hep-th/0212097

Date: 2002-12-09

Title: Topological Effects in Matrix Models representing Lattice Gauge Theories

at Large NAuthors: H. Neuberger (Rutgers)

Comments: 11 pages, LaTeX, Contribution to TH2002

Quenched reduction is revisited from the modern viewpoint offield-orbifolding. Fermions are included and it is shown how the old problem ofpreserving anomalies and field topology after reduction is solved with the helpof the overlap construction.